addERC20Token(address,uint256,uint256).details: Add an ERC20 Token to the list

params._price: The price of this token to AOETH
params._tokenAddress: The address of the ERC20 Token

params._value: the max amount they can spend

params._extraData: some extra information to send to the approved contract

getByAddress(address).details: Get an ERC20 Token information given an address

params._tokenAddress: The address of the ERC20 Token

getByAddress(address).return: The ERC20 Token addressThe name of the tokenThe symbol of the tokenThe price of this token to AOETHThe max quantity for exchangeThe total AOETH exchanged from this tokenThe status of this token

getById(uint256).details: Get an ERC20 Token information given an ID

params._id: The internal ID of the ERC20 Token

getById(uint256).return: The ERC20 Token addressThe name of the tokenThe symbol of the tokenThe price of this token to AOETHThe max quantity for exchangeThe total AOETH exchanged from this tokenThe status of this token

receiveApproval(address,uint256,address,.details: When a user approves AOETH to spend on his/her behalf (i.e exchange to AOETH)

params._extraData: The extra data sent during the approval
params._from: The user address that approved AOETH
params._token: The address of the ERC20 Token
params._value: The amount that the user approved

params._active: The active status for this token
params._tokenAddress: The address of the ERC20 Token

params._maxQuantity: The max exchange quantity for this token
params._tokenAddress: The address of the ERC20 Token

setWhitelist(address,bool).details: Whitelist `_account` address to transact on behalf of others

transferERC20(address,address,uint256).details: Allows TheAO to transfer `_amount` of ERC20 Token from this address to `_recipient`

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfer ownership of The AO to new address

params._theAO: The new address to be transferred

whitelistTransferFrom(address,address,ui.details: Whitelisted address transfer tokens from other address	 * Send `_value` tokens to `_to` on behalf of `_from`

approve(address,uint256).notice: Set allowance for other address	 * Allows `_spender` to spend no more than `_value` tokens in your behalf

approveAndCall(address,uint256,bytes).notice: Set allowance for other address and notify	 * Allows `_spender` to spend no more than `_value` tokens in your behalf, and then ping the contract about it

burn(uint256).notice: Destroy tokens	 * Remove `_value` tokens from the system irreversibly

burnFrom(address,uint256).notice: Destroy tokens from other account	 * Remove `_value` tokens from the system irreversibly on behalf of `_from`.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfer tokens	 * Send `_value` tokens to `_to` from your account

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfer tokens from other address	 * Send `_value` tokens to `_to` in behalf of `_from`
